  "text": "The presence of a well-behaved potential V in the equation facilitates the understanding of the behavior of small solutions, since for such solutions, the potential of the linearized operator is V at the main order. We present from [CITATION_1] a typical result with potential. For a complete list of references concerning such questions, we refer to the introduction of [CITATION_2] . Consider the following model",
